wiki.summary: Tabun (たぶん, "Probably") is the fourth overall single from Yoasobi as well as the fourth from The Book EP. Unlike the singles prior, which emphasized Yoasobi's unique upbeat style combined with bittersweet lyrics, Tabun embraces the more mellow side of the band and distinctly lacks the band's notable bombastic choruses and climaxes, instead favoring a floaty, soft production combined with simple, mellow funky rhythm sections, supporting a restrained performance from Ikura. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Tabun (たぶん, "Probably") is the fourth overall single from Yoasobi as well as the fourth from The Book EP. Unlike the singles prior, which emphasized Yoasobi's unique upbeat style combined with bittersweet lyrics, Tabun embraces the more mellow side of the band and distinctly lacks the band's notable bombastic choruses and climaxes, instead favoring a floaty, soft production combined with simple, mellow funky rhythm sections, supporting a restrained performance from Ikura. Lyrically, the song deals with a couple deciding to break up in the morning, as the two internally reflect on how their love faded away without their realization. Read more on Last.fm.
